Close #31702, #31695

Now `fakeAsync()` only supports timer related macroTasks, such as `setTimeout`, `setInterval`, for other tasks such as
`XMLHttpRequest.send`, it is not supported. This PR adds the functionality to `FakeAsyncTestZoneSpec`.

So we can use `fakeAsync()` to do more `async` tests.

```
        it('should get response with tickXHR', fakeAsync(() => {
             registerNonTimerMacroTaskHandler(
                  (source: string, data: any,
                   taskCallback: (options: {callbackArgs: any[], delay?: number}) => void) => {
                    if (source === 'XMLHttpRequest.send') {
                      const xhr = data;
                      setTimeout(() => {
                        xhr.readyState = XMLHttpRequest.DONE;
                        xhr.responseText = 'response';
                        xhr.triggerEvent('readystatechange');
                      }, 100);
                    }
                  });

              let finished = false;
              let req = new XMLHttpRequest();

              req.onreadystatechange = () => {
                if (req.readyState === XMLHttpRequest.DONE) {
                  finished = true;
                }
              };

              req.open('GET', '/test', true);
              req.send();
              expect(req.responseText as any).toEqual(undefined);
              expect(finished).toBe(false);
              tick(100);
              expect(req.responseText).toEqual('response');
              expect(finished).toBe(true);
            });
        });
      }));
```

The user can control when to trigger the response.

The other example is `FileReader`.

```
   it('test FileReader', fakeAsync(() => {
      registerNonTimerMacroTaskHandler(
                  (source: string, data: any,
                   taskCallback: (options: {callbackArgs: any[], delay?: number}) => void) => {
                    if (source === 'FileReader.readAsText') {
                      const reader = data;
                      setTimeout(() => {
                        reader.readyState = 4;
                        reader.result = 'blob';
                        reader.triggerEvent('loadend');
                      }, 100);
                    }
                  });
              let finished = false;
              let reader = new FileReader();

              reader.onload = () => {
                finished = true;
              };

              reader.readAsText(new Blob(['Hello World!']));
              expect(reader.result as any).toEqual(undefined);
              expect(finished).toBe(false);
              tick(100);
              expect(reader.result).toEqual('blob');
              expect(finished).toBe(true);
            });
```

In this PR, I will add more APIs to support in the `fakeAsync()`

- FileReader
- MutationObserver
- IntersectionObserver
- ResizeObserver
- ...
